Oops!  In my previous post, I accidentally entered the same link twice (the guide for using Praat software to make Spectrograms).  Here&#39;s the correct link to download the Praat software from the University of Amsterdam:

http://www.fon.hum.uva.nl/praat/

Sharon from S.F.

--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, leongbabe@... wrote:
&gt;
&gt; 
&gt; Hey all,
&gt; 
&gt; Here&#39;s another free software for making spectrograms.  The software is called &quot;Praat,&quot; and was created by two authors at the University of Amsterdam.  It contains download links for Windows and MAC.
&gt; 
&gt; http://person2.sol.lu.se/SidneyWood/praate/frames.html
&gt; 
&gt; Here&#39;s a guide to using the Praat software (Click on &quot;Spectral Analysis&quot; and then on&quot;Making Spectrograms&quot; to see examples):
&gt; 
&gt; http://person2.sol.lu.se/SidneyWood/praate/frames.html
&gt; 
&gt; I&#39;ve just downloaded the Praat software and immediately tried it out on an EVP I captured at the Columbarium in San Francisco (final resting place of many cremations).  I&#39;ve attached a jpeg of the Spectrogram of the EVP.  As I&#39;m new to this software, and not familiar with its features, I present the Spectrogram without any editing.  BTW, I captured this image by making a screenshot, pasted it into Photoshop and then saved it as a jpeg.
&gt; 
&gt; Sharon from S.F.
&gt;
